.TH "ea_write" 9 "ea_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ea_write \- writes the request info to an ea, creating new blocks if necessary
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ea_write
.BI "(struct gfs2_inode *ip "  ","
.BI "struct gfs2_ea_header *ea "  ","
.BI "struct gfs2_ea_request *er "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ip" 12
inode that is being modified
.IP "ea" 12
the location of the new ea in a block
.IP "er" 12
the write request
.SH "NOTE"
does not update ea_rec_len or the GFS2_EAFLAG_LAST bin of ea_flags
.SH "RETURN"
errno
